page.title: 02Visiting Plympton St Maurice
page.content: We went for a walk around one of the oldest streets in Plympton called{Fore {Street.}It has got two types of houses they are called{Victorian and Georgian there are three shops in Fore Street the {Printers, antique {restorers}and a{television repair {shop.}Parts of the Victorian and Georgian houses have been knocked down and rebuilt .The buildings in Fore Street quite big and in 1881 there could have been approximatly 14 people living in one house. We went up to the of the ruins of an old {Norman {Castle}and looked down on Fore Street and some of Plympton . We found that the primary land cover was{GRASS}and the secondry land cover was {RESIDENTIAL. By Clare Dickenson, Michael Cassidy, Suzanne Foster and Anna Hockeday.
